512
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:09,791
<i>♪ Let me hear you say
Put that bad vibe back on the shelf ♪</i>

513
00:27:10,666 --> 00:27:11,791
Who's a good boy?

514
00:27:11,875 --> 00:27:13,250
Yes, you are.

515
00:27:13,750 --> 00:27:15,916
The summer
that we went to Mohonk, New York.

516
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:18,250
Ugh. I fished every day in the lake
for two weeks.

517
00:27:18,333 --> 00:27:19,875
I got nothing but a sunburn.

518
00:27:19,958 --> 00:27:21,833
- [all chuckling]
- How do you do that?

519
00:27:22,541 --> 00:27:23,375
Oh, hey.

520
00:27:23,458 --> 00:27:24,916
[John] There he is.

521
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:28,583
The stinky foul beast,
and he brought his dog.

522
00:27:28,666 --> 00:27:30,791
[Ginny] Oh! John...

523
00:27:30,875 --> 00:27:32,708
Oh, you remember the Goodwins, Fielding?

524
00:27:32,791 --> 00:27:35,041
- Yes! Hi.
- [Mrs. Goodwin] Good to see you again.

525
00:27:35,125 --> 00:27:36,750
You were out for a long time.

526
00:27:36,833 --> 00:27:39,333
Yeah, we stopped at Mr. Platt's
so Gonk could play with Yuri.

527
00:27:39,416 --> 00:27:41,096
It's good for him to play with other dogs.

528
00:27:41,125 --> 00:27:44,333
- Yeah. Well, can I make you a plate?
- Uh, o, thank you.

529
00:27:44,416 --> 00:27:45,291
You never eat.

530
00:27:45,375 --> 00:27:48,000
- He's preparing for a life of poverty.
- [Ginny sighs]

531
00:27:48,625 --> 00:27:51,041
- Oh! I got him.
- Hey! Hey!

532
00:27:51,125 --> 00:27:52,666
- That's mine.
- He loves pie.

533
00:27:53,916 --> 00:27:56,541
We're gonna do some yoga
