534
00:27:56,625 --> 00:27:59,458
- It was great seeing you guys.
- [Ginny] Come back and eat, okay?

535
00:28:00,625 --> 00:28:03,166
- You tease him too much.
- I'm just having fun with him.

536
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:05,720
[Mr. Goodwin] Must be nice
to have him home.

537
00:28:05,750 --> 00:28:07,041
[John and Ginny] Mmm.

538
00:28:07,541 --> 00:28:08,583
Yes and no.

539
00:28:09,666 --> 00:28:10,500
Look...

540
00:28:10,583 --> 00:28:14,333
[sighs] I was broke in college.
I worked my way through with three jobs.

541
00:28:14,416 --> 00:28:16,375
And when I graduated, I had employment.

542
00:28:16,958 --> 00:28:20,541
You know, and when my father was 21,
he'd served in a war.

543
00:28:20,625 --> 00:28:23,000
[Ginny] Yeah, but he
just hasn't found his path yet.

544
00:28:23,500 --> 00:28:26,791
[John] Yeah, well, he better,
'cause I will not be Tim Misner.

545
00:28:26,875 --> 00:28:30,041
His son's 35 years old and just
moved back into the house with them.

546
00:28:30,125 --> 00:28:31,708
It's what keeps me up at night.

547
00:28:33,666 --> 00:28:35,666
[dramatic music playing]

548
00:28:37,250 --> 00:28:38,410
[Nate] My class isn't boring,

549
00:28:38,458 --> 00:28:41,166
and the last question
that I asked on the test was,

550
00:28:41,250 --> 00:28:42,458
"Is atheism a religion?"

551
00:28:42,541 --> 00:28:44,750
- Oh.
- I know. Like, how do you answer that?

552
00:28:45,666 --> 00:28:47,666
You can't. It's not a thing.

553
00:28:47,750 --> 00:28:50,291
So, I just gave everybody an "A"
and watched <i>The Office.</i>

554
00:28:50,375 --> 00:28:52,666
Nice. You know,
the thought of you teaching undergrads,

555
00:28:52,750 --> 00:28:54,166
it's kind of terrifying.

556
00:28:54,250 --> 00:28:55,125
- I know.
- Terrifies me.

557
00:28:55,208 --> 00:28:57,916
- [fox chirping]
- Check that out. A fox.

558
00:29:00,125 --> 00:29:02,333
You see the fox? Go get the fox!

559
00:29:02,416 --> 00:29:03,666
[Gonker barks]

560
00:29:05,916 --> 00:29:07,208
[Gonker barks]

561
00:29:07,875 --> 00:29:09,434
- [Fielding] Zoom!
- [Nate] There he goes.

562
00:29:09,458 --> 00:29:11,500
See fox, chase fox.

563
00:29:11,583 --> 00:29:13,833
Why can't my life
be as simple as Gonker's?

564
00:29:13,916 --> 00:29:15,041
I know, right?

565
00:29:15,750 --> 00:29:18,125
It's good to see you.
Thank you for driving up.

566
00:29:18,208 --> 00:29:20,791
Yeah. You sounded pretty down
on the phone.

567
00:29:23,583 --> 00:29:26,041
Your dad's just kidding.
I mean, you know that.

568
00:29:26,125 --> 00:29:27,625
Mmm...

569
00:29:27,708 --> 00:29:31,458
Nah. Like, I always knew
he was disappointed in me, but this time...

570
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:35,041
- I don't know, he just seemed embarrassed.
- He's not. He's not embarrassed.

571
00:29:35,125 --> 00:29:36,458
He's not. He's just...

572
00:29:38,041 --> 00:29:38,875
your dad.

573
00:29:38,958 --> 00:29:39,958
He just doesn't get it.

574
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:41,791
Like, I'm very well aware
of how lucky I am.

575
00:29:41,875 --> 00:29:43,125
- Right?
- I am.

576
00:29:43,208 --> 00:29:44,583
You know, to have two parents

577
00:29:44,666 --> 00:29:47,000
who busted their asses
to send me to school.

578
00:29:47,083 --> 00:29:48,976
- Yes, they did.
- And gave me every opportunity.

579
00:29:49,000 --> 00:29:51,226
Like, I'm just trying to figure out
what to do with that.

580
00:29:51,250 --> 00:29:52,250
What does that mean?

581
00:29:53,041 --> 00:29:55,791
It's hard to find a career
when you're not good at anything.

582
00:29:55,875 --> 00:29:56,750
You are good at stuff.

583
00:29:56,833 --> 00:29:58,208
- Okay.
- Yes, you are.

584
00:29:58,291 --> 00:30:00,041
It's not like I can get paid for kayaking.

585
00:30:00,125 --> 00:30:02,125
- [Nate] You might be able to.
- Gonker!

586
00:30:02,875 --> 00:30:03,875
Come here!

587
00:30:03,958 --> 00:30:05,958
Gonker!

588
00:30:07,875 --> 00:30:09,416
[Fielding] He ran fast. Gonker!

589
00:30:10,041 --> 00:30:11,875
Gonky buddy, ya hiding?

590
00:30:17,291 --> 00:30:18,500
Gonker!

591
00:30:22,791 --> 00:30:24,458
Gonker!

592
00:30:26,083 --> 00:30:28,333
[suspenseful music playing]

593
00:30:28,916 --> 00:30:29,916
[Fielding] Gonk!

594
00:30:32,250 --> 00:30:33,416
Gonker!

595
00:30:33,500 --> 00:30:34,500
Gonk!

596
00:30:36,208 --> 00:30:37,583
Gonker!

597
00:30:40,083 --> 00:30:41,083
Gonker!

598
00:30:43,666 --> 00:30:44,750
Gonker!

599
00:30:44,833 --> 00:30:46,833
[suspenseful music continues]

600
00:30:47,916 --> 00:30:49,208
Gonker!

601
00:30:50,875 --> 00:30:53,125
Mom! Dad! He's gone!

602
00:30:53,208 --> 00:30:55,583
- [both] What? Who's gone?
- [Fielding] Gonker.

603
00:30:55,666 --> 00:30:58,625
- What happened to your face?
- I fell down a ravine looking for him.

604
00:30:58,708 --> 00:31:00,708
- Where?
- [Fielding] The Appalachian Trail.

605
00:31:00,791 --> 00:31:02,541
He went after a fox
and he never came back.

606
00:31:02,625 --> 00:31:04,465
Nate and I,
we were looking everywhere for him.

607
00:31:04,500 --> 00:31:07,208
- He's somewhere out there right now.
- There are coyotes out there.

608
00:31:07,291 --> 00:31:09,331
- They're gonna eat him alive.
- That's not helpful.

609
00:31:09,375 --> 00:31:12,416
This is why I told you to use a leash!
I knew this would happen!

610
00:31:12,500 --> 00:31:15,458
- When was the last time he had his shot?
- Ten days ago.

611
00:31:15,541 --> 00:31:17,750
So he's got 20 days tops.

612
00:31:17,833 --> 00:31:19,833
Fielding, what is wrong with you?

613
00:31:19,916 --> 00:31:21,750
[John] This is what we're gonna do.

614
00:31:21,833 --> 00:31:25,541
First of all, we're gonna realize
that we're not gonna find him tonight.

615
00:31:25,625 --> 00:31:28,541
Right? You're gonna take a deep breath,
we're gonna clean out this cut

