00:31:37,375 --> 00:31:39,166
[dog barking indistinctly]

618
00:31:40,125 --> 00:31:43,125
- [dog barking]
- [somber music playing]

619
00:31:43,958 --> 00:31:45,750
[whining]

620
00:31:52,291 --> 00:31:54,541
[indistinct chatter]

621
00:31:54,625 --> 00:31:55,625
Mom.

622
00:31:56,166 --> 00:31:58,625
Please. It's so cold out.

623
00:31:58,708 --> 00:32:02,291
He's fine. He has a fur coat.
I don't have a fur coat.

624
00:32:02,375 --> 00:32:04,041
He's been out there for hours.

625
00:32:04,125 --> 00:32:07,916
I am not letting that bear of a dog
inside while I entertain.

626
00:32:08,583 --> 00:32:11,916
Now go to your room and be quiet
or you'll find yourself outside with him.

627
00:32:20,041 --> 00:32:21,250
Come on, boy.

628
00:32:22,208 --> 00:32:23,500
Come on, let's go.

629
00:32:25,125 --> 00:32:27,416
[hopeful music playing]

630
00:32:27,500 --> 00:32:29,500
[guests chatting indistinctly]

631
00:32:31,875 --> 00:32:34,375
[guests laughing]

632
00:32:34,458 --> 00:32:36,458
[hopeful music continues]

633
00:32:47,041 --> 00:32:48,416
Nice and warm.

634
00:32:51,416 --> 00:32:53,541
You're my best friend, Oji.

635
00:32:59,208 --> 00:33:02,208
[stirring music playing]

636
00:33:06,208 --> 00:33:07,416
[Fielding] It's insane.

637
00:33:07,916 --> 00:33:09,541
A 2,200-mile trail

638
00:33:09,625 --> 00:33:12,625
and the parks department
only has two rangers assigned to it.

639
00:33:13,125 --> 00:33:14,125
What's going on?

640
00:33:14,833 --> 00:33:17,791
Oh, the library gave us phone books
for every county in Virginia.

641
00:33:17,875 --> 00:33:19,791
- At least I think it's every one.
- Why?

642
00:33:20,291 --> 00:33:21,416
Because I'm analog.

643
00:33:21,500 --> 00:33:24,083
And if I search online,
I'm just gonna print it all out anyway.

644
00:33:24,166 --> 00:33:27,083
That's hundreds of loose pages.
This way, it's easier to manage.

645
00:33:27,166 --> 00:33:28,833
No, why are you doing this?

646
00:33:28,916 --> 00:33:30,541
Because we have to find Gonker.

647
00:33:30,625 --> 00:33:32,545
[John] So we should start
with pounds, obviously.

648
00:33:32,625 --> 00:33:33,892
- Animal hospitals.
- Yeah. Right.

649
00:33:33,916 --> 00:33:37,208
And let's do Rockbridge, Rockingham.

650
00:33:37,291 --> 00:33:38,958
- And Augusta.
- Okay.

651
00:33:39,041 --> 00:33:41,375
Also, every town,
we should talk to the police department.

652
00:33:41,458 --> 00:33:43,017
- [Ginny] Yes.
- Talk to animal control.

653
00:33:43,041 --> 00:33:44,708
We should talk to, uh, churches.

654
00:33:44,791 --> 00:33:47,333
Anywhere people congregate
and go for information.

655
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:49,750
Yeah, local newspapers.

656
00:33:49,833 --> 00:33:50,833
- VFW halls.
- Yes.

657
00:33:50,875 --> 00:33:52,916
Rotary Clubs, Elk Lodges.

658
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:55,083
You're talking hundreds of places.

659
00:33:55,166 --> 00:33:56,750
Yeah. You have a better idea?

660
00:33:56,833 --> 00:33:58,000
No.

661
00:33:58,083 --> 00:34:00,166
Well, there's no other alternative.

662
00:34:00,250 --> 00:34:02,791
I'm gonna stay here
and I'll work the phones, take out ads.

663
00:34:02,875 --> 00:34:05,541
Ads? Don't you think
social media is more effective?

664
00:34:05,625 --> 00:34:07,425
I don't do that stuff.
That's your department.

665
00:34:07,500 --> 00:34:08,833
And search and rescue.

666
00:34:08,916 --> 00:34:11,875
Your mom's gonna hold down
the command center here, but you and I

667
00:34:12,375 --> 00:34:14,208
are hitting the Appalachian Trail.

668
00:34:14,291 --> 00:34:16,541
So if we focus, we work hard,

669
00:34:17,041 --> 00:34:19,000
and make calculated, deliberate decisions,

670
00:34:19,083 --> 00:34:21,333
and I promise you, we will find that dog.

671
00:34:21,833 --> 00:34:24,208
Right? Hurry up, get dressed.
We only have so much daylight.

672
00:34:24,291 --> 00:34:25,291
Okay.

673
00:34:27,250 --> 00:34:29,750
You promise? How can you say that?

674
00:34:30,875 --> 00:34:31,958
Because I believe it.

675
00:34:32,750 --> 00:34:34,750
[intriguing music playing]

676
00:34:45,500 --> 00:34:48,625
- [intriguing music continues on stereo]
- [phone chiming]

677
00:34:53,291 --> 00:34:55,000
It's been over an hour driving.

678
00:34:55,083 --> 00:34:58,083
Should I be prepared
for it to be this quiet the whole time?

679
00:34:59,083 --> 00:35:01,958
I'm checking to see
if Gonker's word is getting out.

680
00:35:02,041 --> 00:35:03,041
How's it going?

681
00:35:03,791 --> 00:35:07,333
Just friends saying they hope we find him,
but nothing useful.

682
00:35:09,416 --> 00:35:12,166
Can we play something
with a little more pep?

683
00:35:13,083 --> 00:35:14,625
I'm not feeling peppy.

684
00:35:16,333 --> 00:35:17,750
This whole thing's my fault.

685
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:23,458
Thanks for doing this.

686
00:35:24,375 --> 00:35:26,250
We haven't accomplished anything yet.

687
00:35:27,250 --> 00:35:30,750
Caesar never thanked his generals
